    <note>Liu(2) Zheng [1178] As investigating censor at the beginning of the Shaosheng period (1094-97), he accused such people as Fan(2) Zuyu [7026] and Huang(2) Tingjian [7111]. He rose to Hubu shangshu (no date), but lost the favorable opinion (yi) of Cai(1) Jing [1649] and was given an obscure provincial post. He later advanced, but ended his career in disgrace. Anhui TZ, 154.9a; XCB, 362.14b, 379.4a; SS, 356.1a; SHY:ZG, 67.8a, 11b. CBD, 5, 3860.</note>
